## Plan: Full 5e Formalization & Character Creation

**TL;DR:** Transform the game layer from a narrative-only AI dungeon master into a mechanically grounded 5e experience. Six phases, each delivering playable value. Phase 1 lays the static 5e reference data (races, classes, backgrounds, spells, equipment, feats, monster templates). Phase 2 overhauls the type system so `PlayerCharacter`, `NPC`, `Item`, and new `Creature` types carry real 5e stat blocks. Phase 3 builds the character creation sidebar wizard on the play page. Phase 4 upgrades the turn pipeline and GM context so the AI respects real stats, positions, and inventory. Phase 5 adds server-side combat validation and CR-tiered encounter templates. Phase 6 wires spellcasting, leveling, feats, and multiclassing into a full progression system. The AI remains the narrative driver throughout — the server just enforces the math.

**Important:** All game data should be sourced from the 5e SRD (CC-BY-4.0 / OGL). PHB content beyond the SRD (some subclasses, certain spells) may need to be referenced by name only or omitted. The SRD covers 1 subclass per class, ~320 spells, ~300 monsters — plenty for a deep experience.

