### Phase 1 — 5e Reference Data Layer

The foundation. Pure static data files — no logic, no DB, no UI. Every subsequent phase imports from here.

**Steps:**

1. Create site/src/lib/game/data/races.ts — Define a `RaceDefinition` type with `name`, `subraces[]`, `abilityBonuses`, `speed`, `size`, `darkvision`, `traits[]` (each trait: name + description + mechanical effect tag), `languages[]`, `proficiencies` (weapon/armor/tool). Populate all 9 races + their SRD subraces (High Elf, Hill Dwarf, Lightfoot Halfling, Rock Gnome, + base variants for the rest). Include Variant Human (feat + floating +1/+1).

2. Create site/src/lib/game/data/classes.ts — Define a `ClassDefinition` type with `name`, `hitDie`, `primaryAbility`, `saveProficiencies`, `armorProficiencies`, `weaponProficiencies`, `toolProficiencies`, `skillPickCount`, `skillOptions[]`, `startingEquipmentChoices`, `spellcasting` config (ability, cantripsKnown[], slotsPerLevel[], knownOrPrepared), and `features: Map<level, ClassFeature[]>`. Define `SubclassDefinition` (branch level, features per level). Populate all 12 classes with SRD subclass (Champion, Evocation, Thief, Life, Hunter, Berserker, Lore, Devotion, Draconic, Fiend, Land, Open Hand). Include ASI/feat schedule at levels 4/8/12/16/19.

3. Create site/src/lib/game/data/backgrounds.ts — Define `BackgroundDefinition` with `name`, `skillProficiencies[2]`, `toolOrLanguageProficiencies[]`, `equipment[]`, `feature` (name + description), `suggestedCharacteristics` (personality/ideal/bond/flaw tables). Populate all SRD backgrounds: Acolyte, Criminal, Folk Hero, Noble, Sage, Soldier, + 7 more standard ones.

4. Create site/src/lib/game/data/spells.ts — Define `SpellDefinition` with `name`, `level` (0 for cantrip), `school`, `castingTime`, `range`, `components` (V/S/M with material description), `duration`, `concentration`, `description`, `higherLevels` (upcast text), `classes[]` (which classes get it), `damage`/`healing` (if applicable, dice notation), `savingThrow` (if applicable). Populate SRD spell list (~320 spells). Organize cantrips and leveled spells separately. Include per-class spell-list indexes.

5. Create site/src/lib/game/data/equipment.ts — Define `WeaponDefinition` (name, category simple/martial, damage dice, damage type slashing/piercing/bludgeoning, weight, properties: finesse/thrown/two-handed/versatile/light/heavy/reach/loading/ammunition, range if ranged), `ArmorDefinition` (name, type light/medium/heavy/shield, baseAC, maxDexBonus, strRequirement, stealthDisadvantage, weight), `GearDefinition` (adventuring gear, tools, kits, packs). Populate full SRD weapon table (~37 weapons), armor table (~13 armors + shield), common adventuring gear.

6. Create site/src/lib/game/data/feats.ts — Define `FeatDefinition` with `name`, `prerequisites` (ability score minimums, race, proficiency, spellcasting), `description`, `effects` (ability score changes, proficiency grants, special abilities as typed tags). Populate SRD feats (~40+).

7. Create site/src/lib/game/data/monsters.ts — Define `MonsterTemplate` with `tier` (minion CR ≤¼, soldier CR ½–2, elite CR 3–7, boss CR 8–14, legendary CR 15+), `baseStats` (HP range, AC range, attack bonus range, damage-per-round range, save DC range), `traitSlots` (how many special abilities), `exampleCreatures[]`. Populate ~8 templates per tier (e.g., Tier 1 Minion: goblin-like, beast-like, undead-like, swarm-like). Each template has stat ranges the AI fills with thematic flavor. Include XP-by-CR table.

8. Create site/src/lib/game/data/index.ts — Barrel export + lookup helpers: `getRace(name)`, `getClass(name)`, `getBackground(name)`, `getSpell(name)`, `getSpellsForClass(class, level)`, `getWeapon(name)`, `getArmor(name)`, `getFeat(name)`, `getTemplateForCR(cr)`.

