### Phase 2 — Type System Overhaul

Expand every game type to carry real 5e data. Backward-compatible (new fields optional with migration defaults).

**Steps:**

9. Overhaul `PlayerCharacter` in types.ts — Add: `subrace`, `subclass`, `background`, `alignment`, `speed`, `size`, `languages[]`, `armorProficiencies[]`, `weaponProficiencies[]`, `toolProficiencies[]`, `classFeatures[]` (feature name + level gained), `feats[]`, `spellcastingAbility`, `spellSlots` (current/max per level), `knownSpells[]` (spell name refs), `preparedSpells[]` (for prepared casters), `cantrips[]`, `hitDiceRemaining`, `deathSaves` ({successes, failures}), `inspiration`, `passivePerception`. Keep all existing fields. Add `VERSION_2` migration path in state.ts that fills new fields with defaults when loading old characters.

10. Overhaul `Item` in types.ts — Replace the `properties: Record<string, unknown>` bag with a discriminated union: `WeaponItem` (references `WeaponDefinition` name + adds current magic bonus, special properties), `ArmorItem` (references `ArmorDefinition` name + equipped boolean + magic bonus), `ConsumableItem` (charges, effect description), `QuestItem`, `MiscItem`. Keep `id`, `name`, `quantity`, `value`. Add `weight`, `rarity` (common through legendary), `attunement` boolean.

11. Overhaul `NPC` in types.ts — Add optional stat block: `statBlock?: CreatureStatBlock` with `hp`, `maxHp`, `ac`, `abilities`, `speed`, `cr`, `attacks[]` (name + toHit + damage notation + damage type), `savingThrows[]`, `skills[]`, `resistances[]`, `immunities[]`, `vulnerabilities[]`, `traits[]`, `actions[]`, `legendaryActions[]`. Non-combat NPCs keep `statBlock: undefined`. The `hostile`/`boss` roles now have real teeth.

12. Create `Creature` / `Encounter` types in types.ts — `ActiveEncounter` with initiative order, round number, active combatants (each with tempHP, conditions, concentration status), and outcome state. `Combatant` wraps either a `PlayerCharacter` or `NPC` with its initiative roll and combat state.

13. Overhaul `Quest` in types.ts — Expand `rewards` from `string` to `QuestRewards` object: `xp: number`, `gold: number`, `items: Item[]`, `reputationChanges: {npcId, delta}[]`. Add `recommendedLevel`, `encounterTemplates[]` (reference monster template tiers for the GM to populate).

14. Overhaul `GameState` in types.ts — Add `activeEncounter?: ActiveEncounter`, `stateVersion: 2`. Add `conditions` reference (encode mechanical effects of each 5e condition: `conditionEffects` map with `advantageOn[]`, `disadvantageOn[]`, `cantDo[]`, `autoFailSaves[]`, `speedMultiplier`).

15. Update `StateChange` in types.ts — Add `spellSlotUsed?: {level, spellName}`, `hitDiceUsed?: number`, `deathSaveResult?: 'success' | 'failure' | 'critical-success' | 'critical-failure'`, `featureUsed?: string`, `encounterStarted?: {creatures: NPC[]}`, `encounterEnded?: {outcome: 'victory' | 'defeat' | 'flee' | 'negotiated'}`.

16. Bump state version + migration — In state.ts, add `migrateV1toV2()` that fills new fields with defaults on every entity in existing game states when loaded. The system should handle V0 → V1 → V2 chains cleanly.

