### Phase 3 — Character Creation Sidebar

A multi-step wizard in the play page sidebar. The player creates their character as the first thing upon entering an adventure.

**Steps:**

17. Create API endpoint [site/src/routes/api/adventure/[id]/character/+server.ts](site/src/routes/api/adventure/%5Bid%5D/character/+server.ts) — `POST` accepts `CharacterCreateInput` (expanded with subrace, background, subclass, spell picks, feat if Variant Human, equipment choices). Validates via `validateCharacterInput()`, calls `createCharacter()`, writes character into `GameState`, saves state, returns character. `GET` returns current character for the user in this adventure (if any).

18. Expand `CharacterCreateInput` in types.ts — Add `subrace`, `background`, `subclass`, `alignment`, `chosenLanguages[]` (for races/backgrounds with language choices), `halfElfBonuses` (two ability names for the floating +1s), `variantHumanFeat` (feat name if Variant Human), `spellChoices` (cantrips + known/prepared spells at level 1), `equipmentChoices` (indexes into the class equipment choice arrays).

19. Expand `createCharacter()` in character-creation.ts — Wire in subrace bonuses (from data layer), background proficiencies + equipment + feature, subclass features at branch level (for classes that get subclass at level 1 like Cleric/Sorcerer/Warlock), full proficiency merging (race + class + background), starting spells for casters, proper equipment from choices (not just auto-pack), languages from race + background + choices.

20. Expand `validateCharacterInput()` — Validate: subrace is valid for race, background exists, subclass is valid for class, spell choices are legal for class+level, feat prerequisites met (Variant Human), equipment choices in range, half-elf bonus abilities are not CHA and are distinct, languages not already known through race.

21. Create site/src/lib/components/CharacterCreation.svelte — Multi-step wizard component. Steps: **①** Name + Race + Subrace → **②** Class + Subclass → **③** Background → **④** Ability Scores (standard array / point buy / 4d6kh3, with racial bonuses shown live) → **⑤** Skills (auto-filled from background, pick remaining from class list) → **⑥** Spells (for casters: pick cantrips + level-1 spells from class list) → **⑦** Equipment (class-specific choices with descriptions) → **⑧** Backstory + Alignment + Languages → **⑨** Review sheet (stat block preview). Each step validates before proceeding. The whole wizard lives in the play page's left sidebar area.

22. Add point-buy system to mechanics.ts — `pointBuy(assignments: Record<AbilityName, number>)` validates total ≤ 27 points, each score 8–15, uses the standard 5e point cost table (8=0, 9=1, 10=2, 11=3, 12=4, 13=5, 14=7, 15=9).

23. Wire into play page [site/src/routes/adventures/[id]/+page.svelte](site/src/routes/adventures/%5Bid%5D/+page.svelte) — On mount, check if current user has a character in `state.characters`. If not, show `CharacterCreation` component in the sidebar (replacing the party panel). Once character is created, swap to the character sheet sidebar view. Disable `/gm` commands until character exists. Show a banner: "Create your character to begin adventuring."

24. Create site/src/lib/components/CharacterSheet.svelte — Compact sidebar character sheet: name/race/class header, ability scores with modifiers, HP bar, AC, speed, conditions, skill list with proficiency marks, spell slots (for casters), inventory list, gold. This replaces the party panel for the active user. Other party members show a compact card.

