### Phase 4 — Turn Pipeline & GM Context Upgrade

Make the AI play within 5e rules by giving it full mechanical context and structured instructions per intent type.

**Steps:**

25. Upgrade `assembleGMContext()` in gm-context.ts — Expand the party sheet section to include: full ability scores with modifiers, all proficiencies (skills, saves, tools, weapons, armor), known/prepared spell list, spell slots remaining, current inventory with weapon stats, current HP/maxHP/tempHP/AC/speed, active conditions with mechanical effects, class features available. Expand the response format instructions to include: `spellSlotUsed`, `hitDiceUsed`, `encounterStarted`/`encounterEnded` in `stateChanges`. Add per-intent-type guidance (e.g., for `attack` intent: "propose an attack roll result, damage, and any effects — the server will validate the math").

26. Add intent-specific context injection in adventure-turn.ts — After `classifyIntent()`, inject intent-specific system message for the AI: for `attack` intent, include relevant weapon stats and target AC; for `cast-spell`, include spell description and slot availability; for `examine`, include perception/investigation modifiers; for `rest`, include hit dice available and spell slot recovery rules.

27. Implement `applyGMStateChanges()` completions — Currently ignores `itemsGained`/`itemsLost` and quest objectives. Fix: process `itemsGained` (create Item objects, add to character inventory), `itemsLost` (remove by name/id), `questUpdates.objectives` (mark individual objectives done), `spellSlotUsed` (decrement slot), `encounterStarted`/`encounterEnded` (create/resolve `ActiveEncounter` on state).

28. Wire game events in adventure-turn.ts — After applying state changes, emit the appropriate `GameEvent`s through PartyKit: `game:state-update` (always), `game:dice-roll` (if mechanic results present), `game:location-change` (if location changed), `game:quest-update` (if quest status changed), `game:character-update` (if HP/conditions/inventory changed), `game:combat-start`/`game:combat-end` (if encounter started/ended), `game:clock-advance` (if clock moved).

29. Handle events on play page — Listen for all `game:*` events on the PartyKit socket. Update local state reactively: animate HP bar changes, flash dice roll results, show toast for quest updates, highlight location transitions, show combat banner when encounter starts/ends. The character sheet sidebar auto-updates when `game:character-update` arrives.


