### Phase 6 — Spellcasting, Leveling, Feats & Multiclassing

The full progression system. This is the longest phase but each sub-step is independently valuable.

**Steps:**

35. Spell slot tracking — On each turn where `classifyIntent` returns `cast-spell`, the GM context includes the character's remaining spell slots and known/prepared spell list. After the AI responds with a spell cast, decrement the appropriate slot. Cantrips are free. Ritual casting available for ritual-tagged spells without expending a slot if cast as a ritual (10 min casting time).

36. Short/long rest — When intent is `rest`, determine rest type from context (the AI or player can specify). Short rest: spend hit dice to heal (up to remaining), recover class features tagged as "short rest recovery" (e.g., Fighter's Second Wind, Warlock spell slots). Long rest: recover all HP, recover all spell slots, recover half hit dice (rounded down, minimum 1), reset death saves. Inject rest rules into GM context for rest intent.

37. Level-up system — Create site/src/lib/game/leveling.ts with XP threshold table (PHB levels 1–20), `checkLevelUp(character)` (returns level-ups pending), `applyLevelUp(character, choices)` — increases HP (roll or average), grants class features from data layer, grants subclass features at branch levels, adds spell slots, expands known/prepared spells, grants ASI or feat at ASI levels. Create level-up UI modal that appears when XP threshold is crossed — player picks: new spells (if caster), ASI allocation or feat selection, any other level-dependent choices (e.g., new skill proficiency for Rogue at 6).

38. Feat system — When a character reaches an ASI level (4, 8, 12, 16, 19), the level-up UI offers: +2 to one ability, +1 to two abilities, or pick a feat (with prerequisite filtering). Feats that grant proficiencies, ability bumps, or special abilities are applied to the character sheet. Feats with use-per-rest mechanics are tracked like class features.

39. Multiclassing — Change `class` on `PlayerCharacter` to `classes: {name: ClassName, level: number}[]` with a `primaryClass` designator. On level-up, offer the choice to take a level in a new class (if prerequisites met: 13+ in the new class's primary ability AND 13+ in current class's primary ability). Compute spell slots using the multiclass table (sum of caster levels). Proficiency grants follow multiclass rules (subset of the new class's normal proficiencies). Update the character sheet to show multi-class levels. Update the GM context to list all class features from all classes.

